Let $x = \angle BAM.$  Then $\angle CAM = 90^\circ - x,$ so
\[\sin \angle BAC = \sin (x + 90^\circ - x) = \cos x.\]By the Law of Sines on triangle $ABM,$
\[\frac{AM}{\sin x} = \frac{AB}{\sin (90^\circ - x)} = \frac{AB}{\cos x}.\]Also, $BM = MC,$ so $AB = 2BM = 2MC = 4x.$  Hence,
\[\frac{AM}{\sin x} = \frac{4x}{\cos x}.\]Then
\[\frac{\sin x}{\cos x} = \frac{AM}{4x}.\]Since $\sin x = \frac{1}{3},$ we have
