solution:
Let the two possible positions of $C$ be $C_1$ and $C_2,$ as shown below.  Then the two possible values of $\angle B$ are $\angle ABC_1$ and $\angle ABC_2.$

[asy]
unitsize (1 cm);

pair A, B;
pair[] C;

A = (0,0);
B = 5*dir(40);
C[1] = (2*B.x - 5,0);
C[2] = (5,0);

